03:15.553 --> 03:18.290
Oh! Oh, God.

03:18.291 --> 03:21.059
I just watched nine
episodes of <i> Breaking Bad.</i>

03:21.060 --> 03:23.260
I got to stop.

03:26.097 --> 03:29.767
You know, you might look
really sexy bald.

03:34.372 --> 03:36.573
You're not shaving my head!

03:37.742 --> 03:39.244
But this is living though, huh?

03:39.245 --> 03:41.112
I haven't moved in six hours.

03:41.113 --> 03:42.914
I can't feel my legs.

03:42.915 --> 03:45.116
I don't care.

03:45.117 --> 03:46.718
Oh, my God, it's 2:00!

03:46.719 --> 03:48.653
Mike, we've wasted half the day.

03:48.654 --> 03:51.288
Oh, don't think of it
as wasting half the day.

03:51.290 --> 03:53.925
Think of it as you have
half a day left to waste.

03:53.926 --> 03:55.193
No, Mike!

03:55.194 --> 03:57.427
Get up! Let's walk
to the farmers' market.

03:57.429 --> 04:00.031
There are two things wrong
with that sentence.

04:00.032 --> 04:02.132
Come on, it'll be fun.

04:02.134 --> 04:03.734
We'll shop, we'll get
some fresh vegetables,

04:03.735 --> 04:04.769
we'll make a nice dinner.

04:04.770 --> 04:06.437
(sing-songy): I'll
buy you a churro.

04:06.438 --> 04:10.040
(sing-songy):
You can bring me one back.

04:10.042 --> 04:13.411
Mike! I want to take
a walk with you.

04:13.412 --> 04:15.346
And hold your hand.

04:15.347 --> 04:18.048
And explore the city
with the man I love.

04:18.050 --> 04:19.649
I know.
Yeah.

04:19.651 --> 04:21.218
I get it.
Yes.

04:21.219 --> 04:23.620
I just don't want to go.
All right!

04:23.622 --> 04:25.056
Get up! Pants on, Pooh Bear.

04:25.057 --> 04:26.357
(groans)

04:26.358 --> 04:27.658
You know the last
time you didn't want

04:27.659 --> 04:28.958
to go somewhere this much?

04:28.960 --> 04:30.261
The flea market...
and who came home

04:30.262 --> 04:32.095
with a Mr. T lunchbox?

04:32.097 --> 04:34.098
I did.

04:34.099 --> 04:36.066
Yeah, you did.

04:36.067 --> 04:37.501
Okay, I can't promise anything
that life-changing.

04:37.502 --> 04:39.403
But I can promise you
kettle corn

04:39.404 --> 04:41.104
and homemade root beer.

04:41.106 --> 04:43.674
In a frosted mug?

04:43.675 --> 04:45.108
We'll bring our own in a cooler.

04:45.110 --> 04:46.877
Makes all the difference.

04:46.878 --> 04:48.645
Come on, come on, come on.

04:53.417 --> 04:56.320
Oh, these morticians
give out some sweet swag.

04:56.321 --> 04:58.055
Uh, look at that.

04:58.056 --> 05:00.324
Coffin coin purse.

05:00.325 --> 05:01.825
Now, every time
I need a quarter,

05:01.826 --> 05:04.161
I'll be reminded that
Canterville Caskets wants my

05:04.162 --> 05:07.296
"rest days to be my best days."

05:07.298 --> 05:09.199
I told you it would be fun.

05:09.200 --> 05:11.068
Funeral directors
might be fuddy-duddies

05:11.069 --> 05:13.537
in the embalming room, but when
the rubber gloves come off,

05:13.538 --> 05:14.938
it's a dead man's party.
Mm.

05:14.939 --> 05:17.273
You know, I-I still can't
believe this is what you do.

05:17.275 --> 05:18.842
I mean, did you just wake up
one day and decide

05:18.843 --> 05:20.276
that I want to put
makeup on dead people?

05:20.278 --> 05:23.113
Yes.

05:23.114 --> 05:25.881
That's a hell of a story.

05:25.883 --> 05:28.385
It was after my
grandma's funeral.

05:28.386 --> 05:30.886
I looked at how they did
her makeup, and I thought,

05:30.888 --> 05:33.690
"Why is Ronald McDonald
in Meemaw's casket?"

05:33.691 --> 05:35.325
Well, it-it'll
traumatize you for life,

05:35.326 --> 05:36.727
but at least you found
your calling.

05:36.728 --> 05:38.361
True that.

05:38.362 --> 05:39.496
Well, you know,
it's just great for me

05:39.497 --> 05:41.364
seeing you in your element.

05:41.365 --> 05:42.699
(whispering indistinctly)

05:42.700 --> 05:43.967
Although I didn't
realize there'd be

05:43.968 --> 05:45.869
so many ex-boyfriends
in your element.

05:45.870 --> 05:47.137
I wouldn't call them boyfriends.

05:47.138 --> 05:48.872
I barely know their names.

05:48.873 --> 05:51.107
Well, they all seem to remember
yours and each other's.

05:51.108 --> 05:52.242
What the hell goes on here?

05:52.243 --> 05:53.743
You know these conventions.

05:53.744 --> 05:56.579
It's about networking
and pressing the flesh.

05:56.581 --> 05:59.716
Mm-hmm, you do know that means
just shaking hands, right?

05:59.717 --> 06:01.785
Is somebody jealous?

06:01.786 --> 06:03.954
No. Baby, I'm not jealous.
(chuckles)

06:03.955 --> 06:05.522
I know what we have
is pure and strong.

06:05.523 --> 06:06.722
(louder): And exclusive!

06:06.724 --> 06:08.058
Of course it is.

06:08.059 --> 06:09.124
Carl, look at me.

06:09.126 --> 06:10.927
All my craziness,

06:10.928 --> 06:12.562
that's in the past.

06:12.563 --> 06:15.031
That girl who chugs
Jager out of urns...

06:15.032 --> 06:17.400
and steals hearses and...

06:17.401 --> 06:20.503
dances naked on top of coffins?

06:20.504 --> 06:23.005
I'm not her anymore.

06:23.007 --> 06:24.541
Well, you know...
(stammers)

06:24.542 --> 06:26.409
let's not throw the baby out
with the bath water now. Oh, okay.

06:26.410 --> 06:29.311
I-I'm not opposed
to a little naked dancing. (laughs)

06:33.483 --> 06:35.818
See? You survived the walk
and the farmers' market.

06:35.819 --> 06:39.689
And I only had to pull you
in the wagon once.

06:39.690 --> 06:42.025
I admit, it wasn't so bad.

06:42.026 --> 06:43.793
But since when did farmers
become hippies?

06:43.794 --> 06:47.162
We bought tomatoes from a guy
playing hacky sack.

06:47.164 --> 06:51.033
I know, I'm starting to think
that organic just means dirty.

06:51.034 --> 06:52.502
Well, thanks for making me go.

06:52.503 --> 06:54.303
Oh, my pleasure.

06:54.304 --> 06:55.972
And thanks for not
causing a scene

06:55.973 --> 06:57.506
when they ran out of churros.

06:57.507 --> 06:58.674
Well...

06:58.675 --> 07:01.344
I appreciate you putting
Splenda on the pretzel.

07:01.345 --> 07:02.711
(laughs)

07:05.247 --> 07:07.950
Next time we'll go early and,
you know, I'll get another one.

07:07.951 --> 07:09.385
Really? You'll go again?

07:09.386 --> 07:10.720
Yeah, you know,

07:10.721 --> 07:12.488
I-I enjoyed walking around,
holding hands with you.

07:12.489 --> 07:14.256
I was a little self-conscious
at first.

07:14.257 --> 07:17.826
But then my hand didn't feel
right without yours in mine.

07:17.828 --> 07:19.862
That may be the sweetest thing

07:19.863 --> 07:21.831
you have ever said to me.

07:21.832 --> 07:22.932
Really? I wasn't even trying.

07:22.933 --> 07:25.099
I was just saying stuff.

07:25.935 --> 07:27.770
All right, you sweet-talking

07:27.771 --> 07:29.338
son of a bitch,
you ready to do this?

07:29.339 --> 07:30.839
Okay, explain it to me again.

07:30.840 --> 07:32.541
Cooking competition, okay?

07:32.542 --> 07:34.643
Same ingredients,
one-hour time limit.

07:34.644 --> 07:37.179
Whoever has the
tastiest meal wins.

07:37.180 --> 07:38.647
Okay, what's the prize?

07:38.648 --> 07:41.216
The winner gets control of the
remote for the whole weekend.

07:41.217 --> 07:42.251
High stakes. I like it.

07:42.252 --> 07:43.985
Okay. You got

07:43.987 --> 07:46.155
buffalo meat,
assorted vegetables,

07:46.156 --> 07:49.324
And the mystery ingredient.

07:49.325 --> 07:51.460
Romanesco... that thing
that you thought looked

07:51.461 --> 07:55.330
like an alien on <i> Star Trek.</i>

07:55.331 --> 07:56.298
You're gonna eat that?

07:56.299 --> 07:58.766
I thought it was
a foot scrubber.

08:01.169 --> 08:04.972
Okay, remember, a tournament
is a marathon, not a sprint.

08:04.974 --> 08:06.408
Play tight, be careful.

08:06.409 --> 08:08.343
And when you got the goods,
go for the throat

08:08.344 --> 08:10.512
and shake them
till they're dead.

08:10.513 --> 08:11.880
Any questions?

08:11.881 --> 08:14.515
Yeah, where the hell's
the waitress with my drink?

08:14.517 --> 08:16.351
Careful with the alcohol, Joyce.

08:16.352 --> 08:17.785
You're gonna want
to stay focused.

08:17.787 --> 08:19.020
Are you kidding?
I'm cross-eyed

08:19.021 --> 08:20.489
till I've had a couple belts.

08:20.490 --> 08:21.556
50 to call.

08:21.557 --> 08:22.557
Call.

08:22.558 --> 08:23.925
Call.

08:23.926 --> 08:25.092
Just saying.

08:25.094 --> 08:26.828
It's not only about
playing the cards.

08:26.829 --> 08:28.262
You also got to play the man.

08:28.264 --> 08:30.198
I've got every person
at this table pegged,

08:30.199 --> 08:31.566
except for seat seven.

08:31.567 --> 08:33.335
I cannot get a read on that guy.

08:33.336 --> 08:36.004
Maybe 'cause he's a lady.

08:36.005 --> 08:39.006
She might want to think
about getting that lip waxed.

08:40.241 --> 08:42.510
Yeah. Call.

08:42.510 --> 08:45.246
Raise 150.

08:45.247 --> 08:47.614
Watch them run.

08:48.783 --> 08:50.185
What did I tell you?

08:50.186 --> 08:52.387
To play with the big boys, you
got to have the bigger pair.

08:52.388 --> 08:55.390
And I'm not talking about cards.

08:55.391 --> 08:57.158
Raise 300.

08:57.159 --> 08:58.293
Joyce?

08:58.294 --> 09:00.527
What are you doing?
I got a monster hand.

09:00.529 --> 09:02.829
What? I like my cards.

09:02.831 --> 09:03.898
All right.

09:03.899 --> 09:06.401
Just know you brought
this on yourself.

09:06.402 --> 09:08.703
All in.

09:08.704 --> 09:10.004
Call.

09:10.005 --> 09:12.307
Aces full.

09:12.308 --> 09:14.541
What do you got, honey?

09:19.113 --> 09:21.314
Guess I had the bigger pair.

09:22.717 --> 09:24.452
What I've prepared for you today

09:24.453 --> 09:26.621
is a pan-seared bison medallion

09:26.622 --> 09:28.489
in a port wine reduction,

09:28.490 --> 09:31.292
paired with a brunoise
of roasted vegetables

09:31.293 --> 09:32.693
and cured pork belly.

09:32.694 --> 09:34.895
You are so going down.

09:36.364 --> 09:39.132
Wow, it sure is
pretty to look at.

09:39.134 --> 09:40.801
Thank you.
You haven't said that to me

09:40.802 --> 09:43.370
since I made you
Mickey Mouse pancakes.

09:43.372 --> 09:44.972
And I'm glad
you didn't make those.

09:44.973 --> 09:47.375
You would've won, hands down.

09:47.376 --> 09:48.876
And what are you
serving today, Chef?

09:48.877 --> 09:50.043
Well, I hope

09:50.045 --> 09:52.013
that you brought your jacket.

09:52.014 --> 09:56.716
Because it's about
to get... chili!

09:56.718 --> 09:58.918
Ah.

10:00.921 --> 10:03.824
Wow, it's very, um...

10:03.825 --> 10:06.093
it's... brown.

10:06.094 --> 10:09.129
Oh, thank you. It was black till
I added that bottle of ketchup.

10:09.130 --> 10:11.030
Ah!

10:11.032 --> 10:13.133
Don't put ketchup
on my medallions.

10:13.134 --> 10:15.902
I won't. We're out.

10:15.904 --> 10:17.304
Mmm.

10:17.305 --> 10:19.306
I was gonna make fun
of you for making chili.

10:19.307 --> 10:22.041
But I can't.
This is delicious!

10:22.043 --> 10:24.111
So, I win?
No, well, no, no. I mean...

10:24.112 --> 10:25.312
it's not just about taste.

10:25.313 --> 10:27.648
It's about presentation
and creativity.

10:27.649 --> 10:29.883
Son of a bitch, that's good!

10:29.884 --> 10:32.418
What... what is that texture?

10:32.420 --> 10:35.688
Kettle corn.

10:36.824 --> 10:39.326
Well... what made you
think of that?

10:39.327 --> 10:42.128
Some fell in.
I rolled with it.

10:44.364 --> 10:46.133
Thank you for such a great day.

10:46.134 --> 10:47.534
Are you kidding?

10:47.535 --> 10:48.769
I had a blast.

10:48.770 --> 10:50.537
You know, I always forget
how much I like you.

10:50.538 --> 10:54.007
Yeah, you're
pretty okay yourself.

10:54.008 --> 10:55.609
We're good together.

10:55.610 --> 10:58.144
Yeah, like buffalo meat
and ketchup.

10:58.146 --> 11:01.881
And apparently kettle corn.

11:01.883 --> 11:04.384
You know, uh, one
day, we won't be

11:04.385 --> 11:06.252
to have these quiet moments.
Ooh.

11:06.254 --> 11:08.655
I know, the crazies are
coming home on Sunday.

11:08.656 --> 11:09.788
No, I mean,

11:09.790 --> 11:11.892
after we have a baby, you know?

11:11.893 --> 11:13.260
Today at the farmers' market,

11:13.261 --> 11:14.494
seeing all those little
kids running around...

11:14.495 --> 11:16.296
Oh, it scared
the heck out of me.

11:16.297 --> 11:17.897
I mean, parents just dumping

11:17.898 --> 11:19.900
their kids off
at that creepy clown.

11:19.901 --> 11:22.602
I'm sorry, but balloon animals
should not have genitalia.

11:22.603 --> 11:24.637
(laughs)

11:24.639 --> 11:27.439
Well, we won't be
those kinds of parents.

11:27.441 --> 11:30.977
Nope, we are not.

11:30.978 --> 11:33.011
In fact, after dinner, uh,

11:33.013 --> 11:34.747
what do you say
we go upstairs and, uh,

11:34.748 --> 11:37.350
take another shot
at making our own kid?

11:37.351 --> 11:39.652
Mike, it's not that easy.

11:39.653 --> 11:42.121
Well, I know, uh, it'll
happen when it happens.

11:42.122 --> 11:45.958
But before it happens,
something else has to happen.

11:45.960 --> 11:48.394
No, I... I mean, it's not easy

11:48.395 --> 11:51.196
'cause I'm,
I'm back on the pill.

11:52.699 --> 11:55.134
What? Sin-since when?

11:55.135 --> 11:57.770
A couple months.

11:57.771 --> 11:59.871
Why didn't you tell me?

11:59.873 --> 12:02.474
I meant to.

12:02.476 --> 12:04.010
Molly, this isn't
like denting the car.

12:04.011 --> 12:05.945
This is a big deal.

12:05.946 --> 12:07.146
I know, I... I'm sorry.

12:07.147 --> 12:08.214
I should've talked
to you about it.

12:08.215 --> 12:09.515
But you didn't.

12:09.516 --> 12:10.549
Mike, I...

12:10.551 --> 12:12.618
Ah, don't.

12:12.619 --> 12:14.253
Can we just talk about this?

12:14.254 --> 12:17.820
It's a little late for that.
Enjoy your chili.

