Hello?

12:40.546 --> 12:42.713
Hello...

12:44.717 --> 12:47.218
Can we discuss this?

12:47.220 --> 12:48.754
Oh, we're discussing stuff now?

12:48.755 --> 12:51.123
'Cause I thought we were doing
whatever the hell we wanted.

12:51.124 --> 12:52.825
With no regard for
the other person.

12:52.826 --> 12:54.193
I'm sorry, okay?

12:54.194 --> 12:55.494
I should've told you.
I just didn't want this

12:55.495 --> 12:57.395
to become a whole big thing.

12:57.397 --> 12:59.030
Oh, you mean like it is now?

12:59.032 --> 13:01.466
Yes.

13:01.467 --> 13:04.936
Exactly how long have you
been hiding this from me?

13:06.271 --> 13:08.307
I went back on the pill
when I went away

13:08.308 --> 13:10.175
for that writer's workshop.

13:10.176 --> 13:11.710
So, you got on the
pill just in time

13:11.711 --> 13:13.844
for the eight weeks
away from your husband?

13:13.846 --> 13:15.547
Look, for the last two years,

13:15.548 --> 13:18.550
I have been choking down
fistfuls of hormone pills

13:18.551 --> 13:20.519
and-and fertility supplements

13:20.520 --> 13:24.221
and drinking
that weird Asian dung tea.

13:24.223 --> 13:26.258
And I don't know...
I just felt crazy.

13:26.259 --> 13:28.326
The ups, the downs...
I wanted it to stop.

13:28.327 --> 13:30.996
And the pill regulates it,
and lets me just concentrate

13:30.997 --> 13:33.397
on my writing.

13:33.399 --> 13:35.066
Well, you've been
back for months.

13:35.067 --> 13:37.167
Why are you still on it?

13:37.169 --> 13:39.404
I don't know.

13:39.405 --> 13:41.640
You don't know why you're still
on the pill or you don't know

13:41.641 --> 13:44.375
if you want kids?

13:47.045 --> 13:49.179
I don't know.

14:04.562 --> 14:06.564
(indistinct chatter
and laughter)

14:06.565 --> 14:07.832
You're not done yet?

14:07.833 --> 14:08.967
Hey, it's not my fault

14:08.968 --> 14:10.634
you busted out
on the first hand.

14:10.636 --> 14:12.570
Yes, it is... you're
the one that busted me.

14:12.571 --> 14:15.273
Oh... I'm sorry.

14:15.274 --> 14:16.507
Play some slots.

14:16.508 --> 14:17.842
Get a manicure.

14:17.843 --> 14:19.410
You know, I didn't come here

14:19.411 --> 14:20.545
to be ignored all weekend.

14:20.546 --> 14:22.980
You promised me a nice dinner.

14:22.981 --> 14:24.981
Oh, don't worry, sugar.

14:24.983 --> 14:26.017
I'll make it up to you. Here.

14:26.018 --> 14:27.819
Go buy yourself something sexy.

14:27.820 --> 14:30.087
I want you all powdered
and pretty for me

14:30.088 --> 14:33.256
when I get done
plucking these chickens.

14:33.258 --> 14:35.225
Well, you'll be done in time
for the show tonight, right?

14:35.227 --> 14:37.294
You're killing me, baby. Go!

14:37.296 --> 14:38.996
Fine.

14:38.997 --> 14:40.565
Me and the other wives
are gonna take

14:40.566 --> 14:42.766
a shuttle to the outlet mall.

14:44.101 --> 14:45.636
(cell phone ringing)

14:45.637 --> 14:47.938
Go for Joyce.

14:47.939 --> 14:49.306
MOLLY: Mom?

14:49.307 --> 14:51.275
It's bad, it's, aw... it's bad,

14:51.276 --> 14:52.675
it's so bad.

14:52.677 --> 14:54.612
Calm down, Victoria.

14:54.613 --> 14:56.080
No. It's Molly.

14:56.081 --> 14:59.617
Okay, calm down and tell me
what Victoria did.

14:59.618 --> 15:00.818
She didn't do anything.

15:00.819 --> 15:02.186
I made the mess this time.

15:02.187 --> 15:03.921
It was... it was all me.

15:03.922 --> 15:05.089
Mike is so mad.

15:05.090 --> 15:07.056
I mean, I've never
seen him like this.

15:07.058 --> 15:08.791
Just tell me what happened.
Ma'am?

15:08.793 --> 15:10.728
No phones at the table.
Hey, give me a break.

15:10.729 --> 15:13.262
My daughter's going through
a real crisis here.

15:13.264 --> 15:15.431
Ooh! Raise 300.

15:16.867 --> 15:19.737
So tomorrow there's
an embalmer's brunch...

15:19.738 --> 15:21.771
- Mm-hmm.
- Followed by talks on

15:21.773 --> 15:23.207
"How to Build a Better Jaw,"
Hmm.

15:23.208 --> 15:25.609
"Drainage Do's and Don'ts,"
and "Abra-Cadaver:

15:25.610 --> 15:27.477
When a Corpse Goes Missing." Mm.

15:27.479 --> 15:29.246
Sounds like a full
day of the dead.

15:29.247 --> 15:30.414
(both laugh)

15:30.415 --> 15:32.516
Hey, maybe we could just
stay in tonight, you know?

15:32.517 --> 15:34.784
I don't know about you,
but after all that walking...

15:34.786 --> 15:36.520
ooh, I got convention feet!

15:36.521 --> 15:38.354
You poor thing.

15:38.356 --> 15:40.324
Why don't you order
a bottle of champagne

15:40.325 --> 15:42.192
and I'll run us a bath?

15:42.193 --> 15:43.759
That sounds like a plan.

15:43.761 --> 15:47.363
I'll pump up with some push-ups,
and meet you in the tub.

15:47.365 --> 15:49.565
(cell phone ringing)

15:51.168 --> 15:52.970
(laughs)

15:52.971 --> 15:55.004
Well, well, well.

15:55.006 --> 15:56.806
Hey.
Look who decided

15:56.808 --> 15:58.675
to break the "don't call me
all weekend" rule.

15:58.676 --> 16:01.877
Although you were my next call
after room service.

16:01.879 --> 16:03.413
I got to talk to somebody.

16:03.414 --> 16:04.347
What's going on?

16:04.348 --> 16:05.782
Carl, you know me.

16:05.783 --> 16:07.884
There's only three things
I ever wanted in my life.

16:07.885 --> 16:10.886
Be a cop, get married
and be a dad.

16:10.888 --> 16:11.988
Yup, that's why I love you.

16:11.989 --> 16:13.290
You're a simple man
with simple needs

16:13.291 --> 16:15.424
who's simply adorable.

16:15.426 --> 16:18.694
Carl, Molly doesn't want
to have kids anymore.

16:18.696 --> 16:19.729
Wait, what?

16:19.730 --> 16:20.897
Of course she does.

16:20.898 --> 16:22.898
Then why'd she go
back on the pill?

16:22.900 --> 16:24.633
Wow.

16:24.635 --> 16:25.868
Yeah.

16:27.203 --> 16:29.839
So, um, that's it?

16:29.840 --> 16:32.641
That's her final decision...
no-no kids?

16:32.643 --> 16:34.811
I guess. I don't know.
I didn't ask.

16:34.812 --> 16:36.746
I'm not really talking
to her right now.

16:36.747 --> 16:38.581
Why the hell not?
I mean, talking to your wife

16:38.582 --> 16:40.450
is the only thing
you should be doing.

16:40.451 --> 16:42.018
Man, that's
what relationships are about.

16:42.019 --> 16:43.953
You know, listening,
being there.

16:43.954 --> 16:45.421
Not abandoning each other
in your time of need.

16:45.422 --> 16:46.488
Carl?

16:46.490 --> 16:48.024
I'm doing my naked dance.

16:48.025 --> 16:49.658
Oop, got to run.

16:58.101 --> 17:00.435
Hey.

17:00.437 --> 17:02.338
Hey.

17:02.339 --> 17:04.941
Just... trying to put up

17:04.942 --> 17:06.641
Mom's drinking trellis or...

17:06.643 --> 17:07.710
more accurately, drinking

17:07.711 --> 17:10.878
while putting up
her drinking trellis.

17:10.881 --> 17:13.249
Look, uh...

17:13.250 --> 17:14.983
I want kids.

17:14.984 --> 17:16.385
I've always wanted kids.

17:16.386 --> 17:17.819
I've been very clear about that.

17:17.820 --> 17:18.855
You have.

17:18.856 --> 17:20.522
And-and you said
you wanted kids.

17:20.523 --> 17:21.957
With me.

17:21.959 --> 17:23.526
And if that's changed,

17:23.527 --> 17:25.760
you got to tell me.

17:25.762 --> 17:29.065
We tried to get pregnant
for two years.

17:29.066 --> 17:31.500
That's month after month
of taking those...

17:31.501 --> 17:32.968
stupid pregnancy tests.

17:32.969 --> 17:36.138
And every time
it came up negative.

17:36.139 --> 17:38.240
I think I just
got scared that...

17:38.241 --> 17:41.043
I couldn't give you
a baby, so...

17:41.044 --> 17:44.280
I started telling myself
I didn't want one.

17:44.281 --> 17:46.281
Oh, honey.
At least,

17:46.283 --> 17:48.150
when I went back
on birth control, it was...

17:48.151 --> 17:50.419
you know, it wasn't my fault
I couldn't get pregnant.

17:50.420 --> 17:52.821
It was the...
it was the pill's.

17:52.822 --> 17:54.156
Sweetie...

17:54.157 --> 17:55.691
it's nobody's fault.

17:55.692 --> 17:58.127
Okay? We're in this together.

17:58.128 --> 18:00.228
Yeah, but what if
we can't have a baby?

18:00.230 --> 18:03.632
I just need to know
that you want to.

18:03.633 --> 18:05.934
I really do.

18:05.935 --> 18:07.836
Okay! Then-then we can
figure out the rest.

18:07.837 --> 18:10.172
I mean, there's
lots of other ways.

18:10.173 --> 18:12.074
There's adoption, there's...

18:12.075 --> 18:13.909
abduction.

18:13.910 --> 18:15.777
I mean, we could've totally

18:15.778 --> 18:17.246
snatched a kid
from the farmers' market

18:17.247 --> 18:19.448
while those parents were
busy sniffing peaches.

18:19.449 --> 18:21.550
(laughs)

18:21.551 --> 18:24.319
I'm sorry this weekend turned
out to be such a mess.

18:24.320 --> 18:28.290
It was supposed to be
about us connecting.

18:28.291 --> 18:31.159
You don't call this connecting?

18:31.160 --> 18:32.460
We just went

18:32.462 --> 18:34.796
from "on the rocks"
to me loving you...

18:34.797 --> 18:37.364
more than ever.

18:40.268 --> 18:43.938
Okay, now that's the sweetest
thing you've ever said to me.

18:43.940 --> 18:46.207
I was kind of trying
on that one.

18:58.162 --> 19:00.664
It is looking good.
See?

19:00.666 --> 19:02.567
You were so worried when
I ripped up those instructions.

19:02.568 --> 19:04.235
But you got to admit,
it got easier.

19:04.236 --> 19:05.235
And a lot faster.

19:05.237 --> 19:06.937
Especially when you
started using

19:06.938 --> 19:08.773
the hammer as the only tool.

19:08.774 --> 19:11.075
It's the ketchup of the toolbox.

19:11.076 --> 19:13.110
Ooh, twinkly!

19:13.111 --> 19:15.946
Oh! This is nice.

19:15.947 --> 19:18.015
You know, I can
really see my mom

19:18.016 --> 19:19.983
getting drunk out here.

19:19.985 --> 19:22.986
Well, at least that'll keep her
out of the neighbor's gazebo.

19:26.657 --> 19:28.225
So, if it really
comes down to it,

19:28.226 --> 19:29.393
you're okay with adopting?

19:29.394 --> 19:30.995
Absolutely. Look.

19:30.996 --> 19:32.563
As long as I can teach a kid

19:32.564 --> 19:35.232
to field a grounder and
throw the curve, I'm fine.

19:35.233 --> 19:36.767
Oh, no, no, no.

19:36.768 --> 19:38.435
I've seen you pitch.
I'll teach the curve.

19:38.436 --> 19:41.104
It's like drawing a shade.

19:41.106 --> 19:43.007
Well, since we are
talking about the future,

19:43.008 --> 19:45.409
I think we should get
everything out on the table.

19:45.410 --> 19:47.311
Besides kids, someday,

19:47.312 --> 19:49.812
I want us to have our own house.

19:49.814 --> 19:52.449
Oh, definitely.
Okay, two stories,

19:52.450 --> 19:55.018
big kitchen overlooking
the backyard.

19:55.019 --> 19:56.186
Yeah, that's perfect.

19:56.187 --> 19:58.155
You can watch me
floating on an inner tube

19:58.156 --> 19:59.623
in our above-ground pool.

19:59.624 --> 20:00.991
"Above-ground"? Really?

20:00.992 --> 20:03.426
Well, if I'm dreaming.

20:03.428 --> 20:05.495
God, I love you.
Of course!

20:05.496 --> 20:06.596
What's not to love?

20:06.597 --> 20:07.764
I don't mind the
farmers' market,

20:07.765 --> 20:09.765
I make a mean chili and I can

20:09.767 --> 20:12.001
build the hell out of a gazebo.

20:17.407 --> 20:19.910
Well, the bench is solid.

20:19.911 --> 20:21.844
I built the bench!
I know.

